    <stitle>SINGLE SPEED REAR AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400810">Figure 10</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <figure id="f1400810" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400810" filename="../figg14/G1400810.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Differential - Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves with punch or chisel for correct alignment in
                    reassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400811">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and lift off right hand case half.</para>
                <figure id="f1400811" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400811" filename="../figg14/G1400811.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Match Mark</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and lift off right hand case half.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thrust washer and differential side gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out cross shaft, pinion mates, and thrust washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove second differential side gear and thrust washer.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If differential side bearings are to be replaced, remove old bearings using a suitable
                    puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400812">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400812" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400812" filename="../figg14/G1400812.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Use Puller</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Inspect all parts, including the machined surfaces of the case itself.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>If any gears are to be replaced, they must be replaced in sets. Inspect thrust washers for scoring
                    and excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When it is necessary to remove ring gear from the differential case, carefully center
                    punch each rivet head. Using a 9/16 inch drill bit, drill through rivet heads to depth shown. Next,
                    use a rounded type punch to drive out remaining portion of the rivet (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400813">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400813" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400813" filename="../figg14/G1400813.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Drive Out Remaining Portion</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Always use a soft hammer or H.D. plastic head hammer to strike punch.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use a chisel to remove rivet heads as damage to differential case may result (
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400814">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f1400814" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400814" filename="../figg14/G1400814.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Do Not Use Chisel</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
